Let's think step by step. To set up a system of equations, we write one equation using the first expression and another equation using the second expression:

\begin{align*} \dfrac{3x-9}{2} &= x+37 \\ 2(3x-9) &= 2x+74 \\ 6x-18 &= 2x+74 \\ 4x &= 92 \\ x &= \dfrac{92}{4} = \boxed{23}. \end{align*}
The answer is: 23.
